p2
VFeast of Annamayya
p3
sVnews
p4
VCommemorating the 507th death anniversary of Tallapaka Annamacharya, his Sankeerthana yagnam was recently conducted. Organised by the founder-managers of Sri Shirdi Sai Baba Spiritual Centre M. Valli and her husband Ramgopal consecutively for the fourth year, it was held in the auditorium of Baba's temple at Seethammadhara.The week-long programme comprised competitions in rendering Annamayya sankeerthans for different age groups, and Sankeerthana by M. Harikal and Sarika, music students of the spiritual centre and Sri Kasturi Narasimha Rao Memorial kalanilayam, Machilipatnam. The yagnam proper was constituted of two hours' recital of the compositions of the saint-singer by disciples of Nedunuri Krishna Murty, Varanasi Venkateswara Sarma and Bhukkapatnam Krishnamacharyulu on all eight days.Chaitanya brothers recitalThese artistes are known for their dedication to the process of learning and singing of hundreds of the keertanas of Annamayya regularly at the Brahmotsavams, Annamayya Jayanthi and Vardhantotsavas held at Tirumala. Helping the cause of building up awareness of these compositions all over Andhra, they achieved the distinction of being recognised together as Chaitanya brothers.This year, they made yet another mark by singing a new set of 250 sankeerthans set to music by eminent musicians Sreepada Pinakapani, his disciple Nedunuri, D. Pasupathi, Garimella Balakrishna Prasad and the like. They were accompanied by M. Satyanarayana Sarma on the violin, Mangalagiri Sridhar on the mridangam, Jayaraj on the tabla and Venakteswara Rao on rhythms on most of the evenings.The yagnam concluded with felicitations offered to the duo by Nedunuri on behalf of the organisers.
